81. Some adjectives form no inflectional degrees, as, idoneus (adapt- ed), ardicus (steep), pias (pious), hostilis (hostile), ferus (wild), rudis (raw), and others. Such adjectives (and sometimes the other adjectives) are compared by means of mayis (more) for the comparative, and mamime (most) for the superlative, as mayis idoneus, more adapted; mammo idoneus, most adapted.
